@page "/accessibility"

<PageTitle>Accessibility</PageTitle>

<h1>Accessibility</h1>
<p class="docs-lede">The template follows Carbon-style expectations for keyboard access, semantic roles, visible focus, and responsive behavior.</p>

<CbContainedList Title="Implemented checks">
    <CbContainedListItem>Buttons use native button semantics and visible focus styles.</CbContainedListItem>
    <CbContainedListItem>Tabs expose tablist, tab, tabpanel, aria-selected, and arrow-key selection logic.</CbContainedListItem>
    <CbContainedListItem>Modals expose role=dialog, aria-modal=true, Escape close behavior, and body scroll lock.</CbContainedListItem>
    <CbContainedListItem>Notifications use status or alert roles based on severity.</CbContainedListItem>
    <CbContainedListItem>Data controls use tables, row selection labels, sortable header buttons, and responsive pagination.</CbContainedListItem>
</CbContainedList>

